column1: To the prince we offered twelve thousand flowers
the Civet stalked mouse and berry alike
Under Starlight Covenant Was Etched Into Flesh And Steel
The People Of The Clay City Watched The Sunset For A Final Time
Between the sound of the exhaust and the cacophony of the engine
The Brackish Tide That Swallowed His Toes
And Drew The Warmth Of Blood From Bone
it was marked with a vow of mind and flesh
Mighty though the force of the tides be
the swimmer's will extends further yet
As We Sang For Their Good Fortune
They marked scars of light in pitch
and beheld as the signet sealed upon our pact
